# ALM v12.0 Command Cheat Sheet

## 1. Environment Setup & Dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## 2. Running Inference & Validation Pipeline (Headless)
Runs the unified ALM validation pipeline (Whisper -> Fusion -> Qwen -> HRE -> WSE -> SPE -> TRE -> SIR) over standard samples.
```bash
python main.py
```

## 3. Launching the User Interface
Starts the Gradio web interface featuring the Three-Tier Intelligence report and the Developer Mode JSON trace.
```bash
python application/app.py
```

## 4. Running Benchmarks
Executes latency and tracemalloc memory profiling on the ALM pipeline.
```bash
python scripts/benchmark.py
```

## 5. Running the Validation Suite (Research Phase)
Evaluates all samples inside the `samples/` directory and dumps results into a CSV.
```bash
python scripts/validation_suite.py
```

## 6. Cleanup Model Cache
Free up storage by clearing huggingface cache (Note: Model will need to re-download next run).
```bash
rm -rf ~/.cache/huggingface/hub/models--Qwen--Qwen3-4B-Instruct-2507
```
